ountaineers-set-for-big-12-outdoor-championships</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Aislinn Frazer and Eva Rinker prepare to start the 800 meters at the WVU Last Chance Meet" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/13/20260503_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT_06608.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University track and field team travels to Tucson, Arizona, for the 2026 Big 12 Outdoor Track and Field Championships, held May 14-16.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/13/20260503_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT_06608.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/13/20260503_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT_06608.jpg"><media:title>Aislinn Frazer and Eva Rinker prepare to start the 800 meters at the WVU Last Chance Meet</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/13/20260503_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT_06608.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:18:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59096</s:story_id></item><item><title>11th-Ranked Mountaineers Playing Elite Defense in 2026</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/12/baseball-11th-ranked-mountaineers-playing-elite-defense-in-2026</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/12/baseball-11th-ranked-mountaineers-playing-elite-defense-in-2026</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Centerfielder Paul Schoenfeld extends to make a great diving catch in West Virginia's 4-1 victory over ninth-ranked Kansas at Hoglund Ballpark in Lawrence, Kansas, on Friday, May 8, 2026." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/12/Schoenfeld-Main2.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – There's an old saying in football that defense wins championships. Well, if that saying also applies to college baseball, then 11th-ranked West Virginia could be onto something really special this year.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/12/Schoenfeld-Main2.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/12/Schoenfeld-Main2.jpg"><media:title>Centerfielder Paul Schoenfeld extends to make a great diving catch in West Virginia's 4-1 victory over ninth-ranked Kansas at Hoglund Ballpark in Lawrence, Kansas, on Friday, May 8, 2026.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/12/Schoenfeld-Main2.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 13:38:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59095</s:story_id></item><item><title>Kelly, Yehl Collect Big 12 Weekly Awards</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/11/baseball-kelly-yehl-collect-big-12-weekly-awards</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/11/baseball-kelly-yehl-collect-big-12-weekly-awards</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Gavin Kelly and Maxx Yehl play against Kansas" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/11/Untitled-1Kelly__Yehl_.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Sophomore Gavin Kelly and redshirt junior Maxx Yehl of the No. 9 West Virginia University baseball team have been named Big 12 Player and Pitcher of the Week, respectively, as announced by the conference on Monday.]]></description><medi